evy/pull/19170","diff_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/19170.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/19170.patch","merged_at":"2025-05-18T06:46:13Z"},"body":"# Objective\r\n\r\nFixes #19150\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nNormally the `validate_cached_entity` in \r\nhttps://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/blob/86cc02dca229662bdfb371a0e5a1716560ea7baa/crates/bevy_pbr/src/prepass/mod.rs#L1109-L1126 marks unchanged entites as clean, which makes them remain in the phase.\r\n\r\nIf a material is changed to an `alpha_mode` that isn't supposed to be added to the prepass pipeline, the specialization system just `continue`s and doesn't indicate to the cache that the entity is not clean anymore.\r\n\r\nI made these invalid entities get removed from the pipeline cache so that they are correctly not marked clean and then removed from the phase.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\nTested with the example code from the issue.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/19170/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/19170/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/comments/2869963128","html_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/issues/19150#issuecomment-2869963128","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/19150","id":2869963128,"node_id":"IC_kwDODf6-U86rECl4","user":{"login":"NWPlayer123","id":3280345,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyODAzNDU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3280345?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NWPlayer123","html_url":"https://github.com/NWPlayer123","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NWPlayer123/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NWPlayer123/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https: